Create Animal Class and also Create Cat Class, Cat should inherit Animal. Animal should have methods like walk(),sound(). By means of inheritance access the Animal methods from Cat class.

package Assignment;
class Animal{
	
	void walk() {
			System.out.println("Animal is walking");
	}
	
	void sound() {
				System.out.println("Animal making a sound");
	}
	}

public class Cat extends Animal {
	
	@Override
	void sound() {
				System.out.println("Cat says meow");
	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
	Cat child = new Cat();
	child.walk(); //accessing parent method
	child.sound(); //accessing child method
	Animal ani = new Animal();
	ani.sound(); //accessing parent method

	}
}

2. Explain about Method Overloading and Method Overriding concept with example program
Method Overloading: it means creating multiple methods with same name but different paramaters in same class
eg: 
package Assignment;
class Overloading{
void sub(int a, int b) {
		System.out.println("Value " + (a-b));
	}
void sub(int a, int b, int c) {
		System.out.println("value "+ (a+b-c));
	}
	}
public class PolymorphismAssign {
			public static void main(String[] args) {
			Overloading obj = new Overloading();
			obj.sub(5, 6);
			obj.sub(8, 9, 7);
		}
		}

Method Overriding: it means changing parent method in child class. Parent and child class must have same method name and parameter
Example:

package Assignment;

class Bank {
	void interest() {
	  System.out.print("Bank interest rate 7%");
	}
}
class Sbi extends Bank{
	@Override
	void interest() {
	  System.out.print("SBI interest rate 9%");
}
}
public class PolyOverriding {
public static void main(String[] args) {
		Sbi rates = new Sbi();
		rates.interest();
		}
}
